code .  ---> Open VSCode
touch hello.md ---> create a file hello.md
git status --> 
    gives error which means git is not initiliazed. To initialize git you should create a new repository

First Command we run in a project 
git init
    Git will Start tracking now 

git status --> 
  this will show us our changes.
  This will show us if it has been staged
  It will also sho wwhat files are tracked by Git.

git add .
  This will add all the changes from working directory to staging area 

git add <filename>
   add file in staging area

git commit -m "initial commit"

If you have to get code from remote location to your desktop.
that is called as cloning



git commit -m "initial commit"
Commits file to remote repository 


git clone https://github.com/prashshenoy1/git-test.git

If you have to get code from remote location to your desktop.
that is called as cloning.
Creates a local working directory of a remote repository 

git branch 
 this will show you all the branches that you have in that folder 

git checkout -b update-name
  this command will create a branch and also switch to that branch 

git switch main 
  This will swicth to main branch if that exists


https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=NUELGzIHT-I

git branch -vv
This command lists all your local branches. For branches that are tracking a remote branch, you will see the remote branch name in square brackets:

git rev-parse --abbrev-ref @{upstream}
If you want just the name of the remote tracking branch for the branch you are currently on:

git remote remove origin
Remove the existing remote:

git remote add origin https://github.com/prashshenoy1/study-git.git
Add the new remote

git remote add new_origin https://github.com/prashshenoy1/study-git.git
Use a Different Remote Name

git remote -v
Verify the remote URL

git push -u origin main
Push and set the upstream branch



